701364f-a.title: Bronx: Jessup Avenue - Jessup Place
701364f-a.text:
(1)
1419 Jessup Ave.., south of the S.W. corner of Jessup Place,
showing the Devoe Cottage. It was built in 1804 by descendants of
the Huguenot family of Devaux. The G.W. Bromley map of 1923 as
revised to September 1932, shows the site to be occupied by a six-
story apartment house, the Devoe Arms.
1907.
Gift of Randall Comfort.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same at a later date, showing the front of the house.
1914.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
Gift of Samuel Landsman.
(3)
An additional view of the same.
1914.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
Gift of Samuel Landsman.
